WEBVTT

00:07.094 --> 00:08.878
male narrator:
Previously on "Briarpatch."

00:08.921 --> 00:10.619
[drill buzzing]

00:10.662 --> 00:12.316
- Hey, Lalo, since when
are you border patrol?

00:12.360 --> 00:13.448
- Couple years now.

00:15.276 --> 00:17.539
- That's a sad thing--funeral.

00:19.323 --> 00:20.281
- What was she doing here?

00:20.324 --> 00:21.325
She had to come back

00:21.369 --> 00:22.848
to this poisonous shithole.

00:22.892 --> 00:24.024
- It's home.

00:24.067 --> 00:25.895
She really wanted
to fix this place.

00:25.938 --> 00:27.636
- Young Detective Dill
couldn't keep her nose

00:27.679 --> 00:28.680
out of Packingtown.

00:28.724 --> 00:30.160
- When was this?
- Three weeks ago.

00:30.204 --> 00:32.293
- You're Harold Snow.
Why are you here?

00:32.336 --> 00:33.816
- I'm just looking
for my bug.

00:33.859 --> 00:35.948
- Who paid you to bug
your landlady?

00:35.992 --> 00:37.689
- Ferness, the ex.

00:37.733 --> 00:39.213
- It's the recording
from Felicity's apartment.

00:39.256 --> 00:40.344
It was encrypted.

00:40.388 --> 00:41.519
I need you to scream.

00:41.563 --> 00:43.217
- What?
- Don't you move, Floyd.

00:43.260 --> 00:44.740
- They can't know
I gave it to you.

00:44.783 --> 00:46.089
- I know it wasn't you.

00:46.133 --> 00:48.091
[gunshots]

00:48.135 --> 00:49.136
- Brattle wants to come in.

00:49.179 --> 00:50.441
- Did he say as much?

00:50.485 --> 00:52.095
- He's living in a van, Cyrus.

00:52.139 --> 00:54.054
- I was sorry to hear
about your sister.

00:54.097 --> 00:55.881
- What is it
that you want, Clyde?

00:55.925 --> 00:58.058
- Something I want you to see.

00:58.101 --> 01:00.321
- He drove me to an
abandoned slaughterhouse.

01:00.364 --> 01:01.844
It was full of drones.

01:01.887 --> 01:04.412
[drones buzzing]

01:04.455 --> 01:06.066
- Figure this out, okay?

01:08.981 --> 01:11.245
[distant bird screech]

01:26.390 --> 01:28.392
[speaking Spanish]

02:01.904 --> 02:04.863
[tense music]

02:04.907 --> 02:11.827
♪

02:16.005 --> 02:19.487
[distant buzzing]

02:39.898 --> 02:42.858
[dreamy music]

02:42.901 --> 02:49.865
♪

03:19.895 --> 03:22.767
[alarm blares]

03:31.080 --> 03:32.212
[alarm continues]

03:43.353 --> 03:44.876
[drone beeping]

03:52.406 --> 03:55.322
[tense music]

03:55.365 --> 04:02.503
♪

04:32.141 --> 04:33.795
[speaking Spanish]

04:57.645 --> 04:58.820
- See?

05:04.782 --> 05:06.654
Ven.

05:06.697 --> 05:08.699
Vamos, vamos, vamos.

05:10.353 --> 05:13.400
[speaking in Spanish]

05:26.413 --> 05:28.589
[car engine turns over]

05:28.632 --> 05:32.201
[funky music]

05:32.244 --> 05:34.725
[Silver Apples's
"I Have Known Love" plays]

05:34.769 --> 05:38.816
♪ I have known love
and love has won ♪

05:38.860 --> 05:42.951
♪ I burned my fingers
on the sun ♪

05:42.994 --> 05:46.563
♪ I have known love
and love has won ♪

05:46.607 --> 05:50.393
♪ I burned my fingers
on the sun ♪

05:50.437 --> 05:51.438
♪ I've been...

05:51.481 --> 05:54.441
[alarm and sirens blare]

05:58.532 --> 06:00.185
- There she is.

06:00.229 --> 06:02.753
Morning.
Take it light.

06:04.233 --> 06:06.583
Breakfast is almost ready.

06:10.413 --> 06:11.980
- Why am I here?

06:12.023 --> 06:14.591
- Well, we had about two drinks
for every hour

06:14.635 --> 06:17.028
the cops held us
at the cemetery.

06:17.072 --> 06:19.901
I tried to drop you back off
at your hotel room.

06:21.163 --> 06:23.208
Did you change the locks?

06:23.252 --> 06:25.254
[bright music]

06:25.297 --> 06:26.647
- What's with the toys?

06:26.690 --> 06:28.518
- It's my grandma's
collection.

06:28.562 --> 06:32.217
This was her house and...

06:32.261 --> 06:35.873
this was her pride and joy.

06:35.917 --> 06:38.093
Don't touch.

06:38.136 --> 06:39.399
You don't like?

06:39.442 --> 06:41.836
- No, I just thought I'd been

06:41.879 --> 06:43.707
kidnapped by a serial killer.

06:43.751 --> 06:46.275
- [laughs]
Nope.

06:46.318 --> 06:48.408
- So, what's the deal here?

06:48.451 --> 06:50.148
You, um, managing

06:50.192 --> 06:52.324
your grandma's doll collection?

06:52.368 --> 06:55.153
- Toy.
It's toy collection.

06:55.197 --> 06:57.460
- Toy collection for her.

06:58.592 --> 07:02.378
- I'll sell them all
eventually.

07:02.422 --> 07:04.206
Death is messy, Allegra.

07:04.249 --> 07:06.513
It leaves a lot of loose ends.

07:06.556 --> 07:08.732
Luckily, you've got
West Texas's

07:08.776 --> 07:11.648
best-dressed estate lawyer
to help tie up yours.

07:11.692 --> 07:13.128
So, let's finish breakfast,

07:13.171 --> 07:14.825
head on down to the office,
so you can sign

07:14.869 --> 07:17.175
for that
life insurance policy.

07:17.219 --> 07:19.482
Oh, God.
What now?

07:21.310 --> 07:24.052
- This is the bug from
Felicity's secret apartment.

07:25.401 --> 07:27.490
Floyd handed it off
to me yesterday.

07:27.534 --> 07:28.926
- Before he committed
suicide by cop.

07:28.970 --> 07:31.276
- I don't think Floyd
killed my sister.

07:31.320 --> 07:32.364
Do you?

07:32.408 --> 07:33.583
- We may never get answers.

07:33.627 --> 07:35.933
He's dead now.
They both are.

07:35.977 --> 07:37.674
- What if the answers
are on this tape?

07:37.718 --> 07:39.502
I think she was undercover.

07:39.546 --> 07:41.112
Laffter told me yesterday

07:41.156 --> 07:43.811
that she was investigating
something in Packingtown.

07:43.854 --> 07:45.508
Strucker got mad at her for it.

07:45.552 --> 07:47.554
She gets
a life insurance policy,

07:47.597 --> 07:49.294
and three weeks later,
she's dead.

07:49.338 --> 07:51.079
- You sound like Floyd.

07:52.341 --> 07:53.385
Allegra,

07:53.429 --> 07:55.649
you might not wanna hear this.

07:55.692 --> 07:57.955
But the woman Colder
eulogized yesterday

07:57.999 --> 08:00.523
was your sister.

08:00.567 --> 08:02.264
At least part of her.

08:02.307 --> 08:04.092
Give her that at least.

08:11.229 --> 08:12.622
- Give me the bacon.

08:12.666 --> 08:15.625
[calm music]

08:15.669 --> 08:22.806
♪

08:26.027 --> 08:28.551
I'm gonna get
this tape decrypted.

08:28.595 --> 08:29.552
And then I'm gonna
go to Packingtown,

08:29.596 --> 08:30.553
and I'm gonna find out

08:30.597 --> 08:31.641
whatever or whoever

08:31.685 --> 08:33.600
my sister was investigating.

08:35.558 --> 08:36.951
You coming?

08:36.994 --> 08:39.606
- If it'll keep you
out of trouble.

08:39.649 --> 08:41.259
Sure.

08:41.303 --> 08:43.958
[banging on door]

08:45.220 --> 08:47.570
- Aw, sweet Christmas,
you found it.

08:47.614 --> 08:50.399
Come on in.

08:50.442 --> 08:52.532
Hell yeah.

08:53.445 --> 08:55.926
- Oh. Hal.

08:55.970 --> 08:58.581
You didn't tell me
we had company.

08:58.625 --> 09:00.757
And it's pudding day!
[laughs]

09:00.801 --> 09:04.282
Uh, I'm so sorry.
It's a work thing.

09:04.326 --> 09:06.763
- Yeah, Cindy's
an independent contractor

09:06.807 --> 09:08.809
like myself.

09:08.852 --> 09:12.595
And overhead is tough,
but passion matters, you know?

09:12.639 --> 09:14.684
Thank you so much
for returning my baby.

09:14.728 --> 09:16.425
- Not yet.

09:16.468 --> 09:17.644
You get it back if you make me

09:17.687 --> 09:19.515
a decrypted, playable copy.

09:19.559 --> 09:20.603
- Okay.

09:20.647 --> 09:22.126
I mean, it's voice-activated,

09:22.170 --> 09:24.607
and the battery won't last
more than a couple of days,

09:24.651 --> 09:26.435
so there ain't gonna be
that much on it.

09:26.478 --> 09:27.654
- Ooh, what do we have?

09:27.697 --> 09:30.047
- So, let's say 100 bucks?

09:30.091 --> 09:31.222
Cash.

09:31.266 --> 09:35.183
- Something sweet and creamy.
[laughs]

09:35.226 --> 09:38.229
- Thank you, and thank you.
Mm.

09:38.273 --> 09:40.841
- I bet that would taste good
all over my body, baby.

09:40.884 --> 09:42.582
- So, this is gonna
take a minute.

09:42.625 --> 09:43.713
Just so you know.

09:43.757 --> 09:45.889
Yeah, I gotta upload it,
gotta decrypt it,

09:45.933 --> 09:47.804
but y'all are welcome to stay.

09:47.848 --> 09:49.980
Cindy's pudding shows
are way better live.

09:50.024 --> 09:51.808
And it's chocolate this week.

09:51.852 --> 09:53.984
- Banana cream, baby.

09:54.028 --> 09:55.551
[giggles]

09:55.595 --> 09:58.728
- Delete the original and drop
it off here when you're done.

09:58.772 --> 10:01.339
- Copy that, compadre.

10:01.383 --> 10:02.993
- So, where are we going now?

10:03.037 --> 10:05.126
- She was collecting them.

10:05.169 --> 10:06.431
Come on.

10:06.475 --> 10:09.609
[dramatic music]

10:10.479 --> 10:13.351
- Y'all ain't sticking around?

10:13.395 --> 10:15.136
It is so hard to make friends.

10:15.179 --> 10:18.095
[swing music]

10:18.139 --> 10:23.710
♪

10:23.753 --> 10:25.755
- You're the reporter?

10:29.019 --> 10:30.499
I have to search you first.

10:30.542 --> 10:31.935
- Aren't you aware, my boy,

10:31.979 --> 10:35.591
that the pen is mightier
than the sword?

10:35.635 --> 10:37.462
- Do you have a sword?

10:37.506 --> 10:39.203
- [sighs]

10:39.247 --> 10:40.901
Do your worst.

10:42.990 --> 10:44.339
- Why don't you
take a load off?

10:44.382 --> 10:46.167
- Hm.

10:47.908 --> 10:49.300
- Okay, now, Mr. Laffter.

10:49.344 --> 10:50.301
[claps]

10:50.345 --> 10:51.825
[groans]

10:51.868 --> 10:54.305
So, what's this thing
you're writing?

10:54.349 --> 10:57.134
Some kind of puffy
profile thing?

10:57.178 --> 10:58.658
'Cause you know
I ain't exactly

10:58.701 --> 11:00.137
looking for the limelight.

11:00.181 --> 11:02.574
- Passion project, if you will.

11:02.618 --> 11:04.141
A series about this mansion

11:04.185 --> 11:07.318
and its more
colorful inhabitants.

11:07.362 --> 11:09.364
Big dreams, tragic ends.

11:09.407 --> 11:11.845
- Hm.
Don't I know it?

11:11.888 --> 11:13.934
Ace Bains still has
his name on the gate,

11:13.977 --> 11:16.458
and his wife paid to have him
kidnapped and killed.

11:16.501 --> 11:19.679
Then she melted down
with the sugar factory.

11:19.722 --> 11:22.116
- Well, that's women for you.

11:22.159 --> 11:23.770
- You ever deal
with the Bains boy?

11:23.813 --> 11:27.077
- Candy Bar?
Oh, no--no.

11:27.121 --> 11:28.992
No, after he was loco parentis,

11:29.036 --> 11:32.474
he, uh--
he went just plain loco.

11:32.517 --> 11:35.346
Yeah, he gave up his
inheritance and this house.

11:35.390 --> 11:38.698
- Seems like the dark history
don't bother you.

11:38.741 --> 11:40.917
- Ah, hell, it's invigorating.

11:40.961 --> 11:42.745
Shoot, do you know
how far I had to climb

11:42.789 --> 11:44.529
to make it this high?

11:44.573 --> 11:47.097
I ain't exactly in the business
of looking down.

11:47.141 --> 11:48.011
- Hm.

11:48.055 --> 11:50.100
- Say.
[snaps fingers]

11:50.144 --> 11:53.190
How'd you like to see
Doc Cherry's secret tooth room?

11:54.496 --> 11:55.976
- [laughs]

11:56.019 --> 11:59.109
[traditional string music]

11:59.153 --> 12:00.850
- [sighs]

12:02.591 --> 12:04.506
- Is that a nacho bar?

12:04.549 --> 12:05.812
[laughs]

12:05.855 --> 12:07.422
- For two?

12:07.465 --> 12:10.294
Free refills on duck sauce
and quesobefore noon.

12:10.338 --> 12:12.644
- Hi, Grace.

12:12.688 --> 12:13.863
- Jesus Christ.
[laughs]

12:13.907 --> 12:15.822
Allegra Dill.

12:15.865 --> 12:18.389
Look at you all cleaned up.

12:18.433 --> 12:20.652
Don't tell me you're
back for the reunion.

12:20.696 --> 12:23.655
- No, I'm here for my sister.

12:23.699 --> 12:24.918
- Oh, crap.
[sighs]

12:24.961 --> 12:27.224
Felicity, I'm real sorry.

12:28.791 --> 12:29.749
- Thanks.

12:29.792 --> 12:30.967
- Grace Chow.

12:31.011 --> 12:33.230
I went to high school
with this one.

12:33.274 --> 12:34.275
- A.D. Singe.

12:34.318 --> 12:37.495
I want to hear
absolutely everything.

12:37.539 --> 12:40.672
- Bangs to...here.

12:40.716 --> 12:42.109
- Stop.

12:42.152 --> 12:43.763
- They were actually
like to here.

12:43.806 --> 12:44.938
[both chuckle]

12:44.981 --> 12:46.940
- Did you see my sister much?

12:46.983 --> 12:49.333
- Yeah.
She came in all the time.

12:49.377 --> 12:51.161
Take out.
Kung pao, no peanuts.

12:51.205 --> 12:52.772
- She ever just eat here?

12:52.815 --> 12:54.077
- Sometimes.

12:54.121 --> 12:56.776
She'd park herself
by the window with a book.

12:59.691 --> 13:01.171
- How's the neighborhood?

13:01.215 --> 13:02.912
- It's gone south in a hurry.

13:02.956 --> 13:05.045
And it was already Patagonia.

13:05.088 --> 13:07.308
It turned when
the Dunjee Brewery closed.

13:07.351 --> 13:08.613
- It closed?

13:08.657 --> 13:10.528
I just drank four
of those beers yesterday.

13:10.572 --> 13:12.008
- They still make them.

13:12.052 --> 13:14.228
Dunjee just outsourced
the brewing to Mexico.

13:14.271 --> 13:16.883
- That sounds like Texas.

13:16.926 --> 13:19.189
- Not exactly a killer view.

13:20.582 --> 13:23.454
[light dramatic music]

13:23.498 --> 13:24.978
♪

13:25.021 --> 13:28.242
- The slaughterhouse.

13:28.285 --> 13:31.158
Did Felicity sit in this seat
the last time she was here?

13:31.201 --> 13:33.116
About three weeks ago?

13:33.160 --> 13:35.466
- She was here until closing.

13:36.511 --> 13:38.513
- I saw something here
the other night.

13:38.556 --> 13:40.080
Felicity was staking
this place out.

13:40.123 --> 13:42.517
She must have
seen something too.

13:42.560 --> 13:44.824
But now...

13:48.262 --> 13:50.307
- What am I
supposed to be seeing?

13:50.351 --> 13:54.224
- There were drones in here.
Dozens of them.

13:54.268 --> 13:55.922
Clyde Brattle dropped me off
here so I could see them,

13:55.965 --> 13:57.924
and now they're gone.

13:57.967 --> 14:00.013
- Clyde Brattle,
AKA "The Dapper Philadelphian,"

14:00.056 --> 14:03.407
and the target of your
Senator's big hearing.

14:03.451 --> 14:04.931
You're my client.
Gotta know who I'm defending.

14:04.974 --> 14:06.323
- I don't need defending.

14:06.367 --> 14:08.586
- From where I stand,
it's only a matter of time.

14:08.630 --> 14:12.025
So, you wanna catch me up
on what you're doing here?

14:12.068 --> 14:13.940
- The Feds were supposed
to detain Brattle

14:13.983 --> 14:15.724
while I secured
Jake Spivey's testimony,

14:15.767 --> 14:18.118
but now Jake won't
talk, and...

14:18.161 --> 14:20.337
Brattle wants the same deal.

14:20.381 --> 14:22.122
- So, what does any of this
have to do with Felicity?

14:22.165 --> 14:25.125
- Nothing, or so I thought.

14:25.168 --> 14:27.605
Brattle's not the type
to get his hands dirty.

14:27.649 --> 14:30.217
He's into mind games

14:30.260 --> 14:32.349
and medium-sized coups.

14:33.829 --> 14:36.223
I think Felicity

14:36.266 --> 14:39.139
found something in here, and...

14:39.182 --> 14:42.664
whatever it is, Brattle
wanted me to see it, too.

14:42.707 --> 14:44.187
- Why?

14:44.231 --> 14:46.363
- Maybe because he knows
my history with Jake,

14:46.407 --> 14:47.887
and he wanted
to give me something

14:47.930 --> 14:49.932
to get me on his side.

14:49.976 --> 14:51.020
- So, how do we go about

14:51.064 --> 14:51.978
seeing something
that isn't here anymore?

14:52.021 --> 14:53.022
[crash]

14:53.066 --> 14:54.371
- Somebody's here.

14:54.415 --> 14:56.460
- Allegra.

14:56.504 --> 14:57.897
- Hey!

15:03.293 --> 15:04.468
[groans]

15:04.512 --> 15:05.513
- Who was that?

15:05.556 --> 15:07.210
- Damn it.

15:07.254 --> 15:10.387
That was the cleanup crew.

15:10.431 --> 15:12.346
[sighs]

15:12.389 --> 15:14.130
- [burps, sighs]

15:14.174 --> 15:15.915
At the funeral, Eve?

15:15.958 --> 15:18.221
At the fucking funeral?

15:18.265 --> 15:20.658
- I said I'd catch my man,
and I did.

15:20.702 --> 15:22.225
- Don't get cute with me.

15:22.269 --> 15:24.314
I don't pay for cute.

15:25.576 --> 15:27.665
So, is the Dill case done,
or what?

15:27.709 --> 15:28.753
- More or less, yeah.

15:28.797 --> 15:30.886
Family's still in town.

15:30.930 --> 15:32.235
There's a sister.

15:32.279 --> 15:33.933
- A sister?
That don't count.

15:33.976 --> 15:35.935
Nobody gives a shit
about a sister.

15:35.978 --> 15:37.371
I got a sister.

15:37.414 --> 15:39.286
She's got shingles,
three stepkids,

15:39.329 --> 15:41.592
lives in a double wide
just outside of Fort Bliss.

15:41.636 --> 15:42.854
- I didn't know that.

15:42.898 --> 15:43.986
- Of course you didn't.

15:44.030 --> 15:45.379
'Cause it doesn't
fucking matter.

15:45.422 --> 15:47.990
Now, I need this business
to go away quickly.

15:48.034 --> 15:49.557
- It'll all be wrapped up
shortly, sir,

15:49.600 --> 15:50.950
and I think you're
gonna be real happy.

15:50.993 --> 15:51.994
- You know what makes me happy?

15:52.038 --> 15:54.257
Very happy?

15:54.301 --> 15:56.607
A glass of añejoin one hand.

15:56.651 --> 15:59.697
And the back of a stripper's
head in the other.

15:59.741 --> 16:01.961
'Cause the stripper's--
- I get it, Tony.

16:02.004 --> 16:03.788
I get it.
- Good.

16:03.832 --> 16:07.270
'Cause there's something else.

16:07.314 --> 16:09.446
I need you looking
into Packingtown.

16:11.579 --> 16:14.103
Some company's buying up
tracks of land.

16:14.147 --> 16:16.976
"Durango Global."

16:17.019 --> 16:19.717
Sounds Mexican to me,
but I can't be sure.

16:21.371 --> 16:24.244
Salazar is a Castilian name.

16:24.287 --> 16:26.376
Anyway, Old Man Staghorne's

16:26.420 --> 16:28.378
got his adult diapers
in a twist,

16:28.422 --> 16:30.772
and I need you to find out
who these bastards are.

16:34.210 --> 16:36.778
- Well, that's not my job,
Mr. Mayor.

16:38.084 --> 16:39.999
- Listen.

16:42.088 --> 16:44.003
If I tell you to do something,

16:44.046 --> 16:47.049
then ipso facto mumbo jumbo

16:47.093 --> 16:49.704
it's your fucking job.

16:49.747 --> 16:51.097
You understand?

16:52.446 --> 16:54.709
- Yes.
- Yes what?

16:54.752 --> 16:57.842
- Yes.
I understand.

16:57.886 --> 16:59.844
Mr. Mayor, sir.

16:59.888 --> 17:01.411
- That's better.

17:04.153 --> 17:05.981
You know, Eve?

17:06.025 --> 17:07.765
You really ought to smile more.

17:17.253 --> 17:18.950
[door closes]

17:18.994 --> 17:21.910
[slow swing music]

17:21.953 --> 17:29.048
♪

17:45.803 --> 17:47.892
- [exhales]

17:47.936 --> 17:50.199
- So, Mr. Spivey,

17:50.243 --> 17:53.115
what kind of rich
do you intend to be?

17:53.159 --> 17:54.551
Lavish rich?

17:54.595 --> 17:55.944
Gaudy rich?

17:55.987 --> 17:57.119
Screw you rich?

17:57.163 --> 17:58.555
- [chuckles]

17:58.599 --> 18:02.777
Well, uh, I guess I'm aiming
for benevolent rich.

18:02.820 --> 18:04.257
- Mm.
- Yeah.

18:04.300 --> 18:06.302
You know, I came back
to San Bonifacio

18:06.346 --> 18:08.261
to build something special.

18:08.304 --> 18:11.177
- Well, that's
mighty admirable of you,

18:11.220 --> 18:14.093
considering your beginnings.
Dirt poor.

18:14.136 --> 18:17.792
Your dad torn apart on the...

18:17.835 --> 18:20.142
slaughterhouse floor.

18:24.973 --> 18:27.236
- [exhales]

18:27.976 --> 18:31.849
- Took decades for me to
figure out how this town works.

18:31.893 --> 18:34.722
- Know what they offered us?

18:34.765 --> 18:35.679
A settlement.

18:35.723 --> 18:38.465
- Year's worth of ground chuck.

18:38.508 --> 18:40.728
You had to cut your own path
in this world, Spivey,

18:40.771 --> 18:42.033
but look at you now.

18:42.077 --> 18:44.775
Money, cars,
community standing,

18:44.819 --> 18:47.822
and a host of armed narcos
to help you hold onto it.

18:49.171 --> 18:50.433
- They're not narcos.

18:50.477 --> 18:52.087
- But they'd have to be.

18:52.131 --> 18:53.784
To protect you
from Clyde Brattle.

18:56.135 --> 18:58.093
- [sighs]

18:58.137 --> 19:00.313
Now.

19:03.011 --> 19:07.233
Why'd you have to go and ruin
a perfectly nice afternoon

19:07.276 --> 19:08.930
with a name like that?

19:08.973 --> 19:11.628
- I'm only saying that
a former Black Ops killer...

19:11.672 --> 19:13.239
- I was military intelligence.

19:13.282 --> 19:15.284
- Whose former partner's
on the loose...

19:15.328 --> 19:16.372
- Clyde wasn't my partner.

19:16.416 --> 19:18.069
- Oh, that's right.

19:18.113 --> 19:20.507
He was your superior.

19:20.550 --> 19:22.335
Which is why he got a bigger
slice of the profits

19:22.378 --> 19:25.947
from Al-Namur.

19:25.990 --> 19:27.688
You know, it's interesting.

19:27.731 --> 19:29.777
My official sources tell me
that those rebels

19:29.820 --> 19:32.432
were killed by loyalist
forces in the retreat.

19:32.475 --> 19:34.477
But my unofficial sources

19:34.521 --> 19:37.001
say something quite different.

19:37.045 --> 19:40.483
- You'd better watch yourself.

19:40.527 --> 19:42.268
- The residents
of San Bonifacio

19:42.311 --> 19:45.706
deserve to know whether the
richest man in their community

19:45.749 --> 19:47.360
is putting their lives at risk,

19:47.403 --> 19:48.970
just by being there.

19:50.667 --> 19:54.193
And what about
these police bombings?

19:54.236 --> 19:56.238
- What about 'em?

19:56.282 --> 19:58.675
- Touched a nerve, did I?

19:58.719 --> 20:00.329
Well....

20:00.373 --> 20:03.071
that's what journalism's
meant to do.

20:03.114 --> 20:05.987
Comfort the afflicted,
and afflict the comfortable.

20:13.429 --> 20:15.997
- Hold it for just a moment,
Chuckles.

20:16.040 --> 20:17.694
My guests are here.

20:21.002 --> 20:22.133
Misters Staghornes, sirs.

20:22.177 --> 20:23.526
- Hello.

20:23.570 --> 20:24.788
- So glad you could make it.
- Good to see you.

20:24.832 --> 20:26.921
- Course y'all both
know Freddie.

20:26.964 --> 20:29.228
- That Boy Reporter.

20:29.271 --> 20:30.968
What's he doing here?

20:31.012 --> 20:33.710
- Uh, believe the word for it,
sir, is freelancing.

20:33.754 --> 20:35.582
- Mr. Staghorne--
- Freddie.

20:35.625 --> 20:38.367
You've been warned about
bothering important people.

20:38.411 --> 20:39.368
- I was just leaving.

20:39.412 --> 20:40.413
- You're on the police beat,

20:40.456 --> 20:41.544
not society.

20:41.588 --> 20:43.285
Go on.
Get back to the office.

20:43.329 --> 20:45.374
We need a new draft
of your story

20:45.418 --> 20:47.202
for the evening edition,
so go, go on, get out.

20:47.246 --> 20:48.203
- Right away.

20:48.247 --> 20:51.337
- And throw away that hat!

20:59.170 --> 21:00.607
- [exhales]

21:03.044 --> 21:05.089
- Well, you see, Chuckles.

21:05.133 --> 21:08.397
You ain't the only one
who knows how this town works.

21:20.583 --> 21:23.325
[Amon Duul II's
"Archy the Robot" plays]

21:23.369 --> 21:25.284
♪

21:25.327 --> 21:26.981
- Drop the bag.

21:28.504 --> 21:30.201
- You think you'll find
the kid here?

21:30.245 --> 21:31.725
- No.

21:31.768 --> 21:34.118
But there's somebody
here who knows.

21:34.162 --> 21:37.687
♪ I've got a robot

21:37.731 --> 21:41.648
♪ It's a friend of mine

21:41.691 --> 21:45.478
♪ I call it Archy

21:45.521 --> 21:49.743
♪ Since quite a long time

21:49.786 --> 21:51.135
♪ Archy is my...

21:51.179 --> 21:52.180
- Mein gott.

21:52.223 --> 21:54.487
My little pickle returns.

21:54.530 --> 21:56.053
- Hello, Gunter.

21:56.097 --> 21:59.535
- Hello.
[chuckles]

21:59.579 --> 22:02.364
I hear you went straight.

22:02.408 --> 22:03.974
- I work for the government.

22:04.018 --> 22:05.280
- Ah.

22:05.324 --> 22:06.542
- This is Gunter.

22:06.586 --> 22:08.762
I used to work for him.

22:08.805 --> 22:11.417
- My name is A.D. Singe,
like "Scorch,", I'm a--

22:11.460 --> 22:14.985
- Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.
What did you bring me?

22:15.029 --> 22:16.813
- We've got some questions
about the slaughterhouse.

22:16.857 --> 22:18.989
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.
Later, later, later.

22:21.775 --> 22:24.691
Oh, you remember my favorite.

22:24.734 --> 22:26.257
[laughs]

22:26.301 --> 22:27.258
[sniffs]

22:27.302 --> 22:28.869
Uh.

22:28.912 --> 22:31.132
You still fight?

22:32.916 --> 22:34.048
- When I have to.

22:34.091 --> 22:37.007
- This one--she had
a mean right hook.

22:37.051 --> 22:40.097
It was like lightning.
They never knew what hit them.

22:40.141 --> 22:42.361
Bam, bang!
[laughs]

22:42.404 --> 22:44.624
Those were the days,
Pickle, huh?

22:44.667 --> 22:46.321
But you had one weakness.

22:46.365 --> 22:49.019
And that was
your biggest enemy, huh?

22:49.063 --> 22:50.630
Her temper.

22:50.673 --> 22:53.720
When the blood gets pumping,
and the adrenaline kicked in,

22:53.763 --> 22:56.679
you would do
the worst mistakes.

22:57.854 --> 22:59.943
- Let's focus on the present.

22:59.987 --> 23:01.684
- Oh, you remember
what your mother said

23:01.728 --> 23:05.122
about our sinful little
Packingtown?

23:05.166 --> 23:06.297
[chuckles]

23:06.341 --> 23:10.214
That we were
"behind God's back!"

23:10.258 --> 23:11.607
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.

23:11.651 --> 23:12.913
- I'll be back tonight.

23:12.956 --> 23:14.044
- All right.

23:15.829 --> 23:18.440
Good, good, good.
[chuckles]

23:18.484 --> 23:20.703
Such a sad woman,
your mother, huh?

23:20.747 --> 23:23.445
Always...
[imitating chatter].

23:23.489 --> 23:25.665
It's good.
All is good.

23:25.708 --> 23:27.362
- What about
the slaughterhouse?

23:27.406 --> 23:31.366
- You don't know
about the slaughterhouse?

23:31.410 --> 23:34.021
I thought you worked
for government.

23:34.064 --> 23:35.326
Should be here.

23:35.370 --> 23:37.981
Slaughterhouse,
slaughterhouse, slaughter--

23:38.025 --> 23:39.722
here.

23:42.464 --> 23:45.424
[dramatic music]

23:45.467 --> 23:52.605
♪

23:55.956 --> 23:58.437
[moans]

23:58.480 --> 24:00.308
- It was drugs.

24:00.351 --> 24:01.875
- A big bust.

24:01.918 --> 24:04.573
Cops everywhere for weeks.

24:04.617 --> 24:07.881
So bad for business, huh?

24:07.924 --> 24:10.100
Then, a couple months later,

24:10.144 --> 24:12.015
another company moves in--
Durango Something--

24:12.059 --> 24:14.278
and they buy
the slaughterhouse.

24:14.322 --> 24:16.498
But they leave it empty.

24:16.542 --> 24:17.630
- This is dated
from a year ago.

24:17.673 --> 24:18.805
What about recently?

24:18.848 --> 24:23.113
- I don't know.
My memory is bad, Pickle.

24:23.157 --> 24:24.463
Yeah.

24:26.639 --> 24:28.162
- Bullshit.

24:29.424 --> 24:31.687
- Okay.

24:31.731 --> 24:33.080
Remember your temper.

24:33.123 --> 24:35.125
[both chuckle]

24:35.169 --> 24:38.912
Well, someone was still working
there after the bust,

24:38.955 --> 24:40.304
but only nights.

24:40.348 --> 24:42.829
And they scrubbed it clean.

24:44.265 --> 24:46.397
- [clears throat]

24:46.441 --> 24:48.791
One more question.
- Mm-hmm.

24:48.835 --> 24:50.750
- Where do the kids
hang out these days?

24:50.793 --> 24:53.361
- The kids?
I don't know any kids.

24:53.404 --> 24:55.581
They couldn't prove it.
[chuckles]

24:55.624 --> 24:58.714
[tense music]

24:59.585 --> 25:02.501
- No.

25:02.544 --> 25:05.504
I mean the kids like me.

25:05.547 --> 25:07.767
- Oh, you mean hood rats

25:07.810 --> 25:09.595
with a death wish?

25:09.638 --> 25:11.901
Well, that I can talk about.

25:13.642 --> 25:15.339
Have a seat.

25:15.383 --> 25:18.299
- Okay, score one for you.

25:19.735 --> 25:21.824
So, if there was a drug bust
at the slaughterhouse,

25:21.868 --> 25:23.870
does that mean
Spivey was involved?

25:23.913 --> 25:25.001
- No.

25:25.045 --> 25:26.960
We've been investigating
Jake for months.

25:27.003 --> 25:28.527
Drug trafficking isn't his M.O.

25:28.570 --> 25:30.616
- Okay, so, who was running
something out of that place?

25:30.659 --> 25:32.835
[indistinct chatter]

25:32.879 --> 25:35.359
[light dramatic music]

25:35.403 --> 25:37.274
[laughter, chatter]

25:39.712 --> 25:41.670
- Fucking bitch.
- Hey.

25:41.714 --> 25:43.019
- Little boy.

25:43.063 --> 25:44.804
- Lil' mama,
I'll show you how big I am.

25:44.847 --> 25:47.415
- You already have.

25:47.458 --> 25:49.243
So why'd you go back?

25:49.286 --> 25:50.636
To the slaughterhouse?

25:52.202 --> 25:54.988
You did a shit job
of destroying the evidence.

25:55.031 --> 25:57.251
Whoever paid you
won't be too happy.

25:57.294 --> 25:58.557
Who was it?

26:01.951 --> 26:04.737
Let's not draw this out, okay?

26:04.780 --> 26:07.914
Pile's cold, which means
you burned it last night.

26:07.957 --> 26:11.047
So, maybe you forgot something.
It happens.

26:11.091 --> 26:14.355
- Bitch, my gang
will fuck you up.

26:14.398 --> 26:17.837
- You're not a gang.
You're just bored.

26:17.880 --> 26:19.229
- Okay, Allegra,
they just kids, come on--

26:19.273 --> 26:21.623
- My guess is that
you went back for you.

26:21.667 --> 26:23.059
- Mm.

26:23.103 --> 26:25.235
- For something you
didn't want anyone to see.

26:25.279 --> 26:26.889
[lid slams shut]

26:32.939 --> 26:34.636
- Yo, what the fuck.

26:34.680 --> 26:35.594
[whispering]
Give it back.

26:35.637 --> 26:37.334
Okay, come on.

26:37.378 --> 26:39.423
Come on.
- Cute.

26:39.467 --> 26:41.077
- Pussy.

26:41.121 --> 26:44.690
- Shut the fuck up, man.
It's for my sister.

26:46.779 --> 26:50.609
Hey!
Where did you even come from?

26:50.652 --> 26:52.872
- Here.
I'm from here.

26:54.134 --> 26:56.310
- You literally stole
a toy from a kid.

26:56.353 --> 26:57.920
Congratulations.

26:57.964 --> 26:59.922
- I've seen this tiger before.

26:59.966 --> 27:03.665
- I knew it was trouble
the instant she walked in.

27:03.709 --> 27:06.668
She was an ex.
My ex.

27:06.712 --> 27:10.629
And she had always been
my unknown.

27:12.543 --> 27:14.850
[harp strumming]

27:16.765 --> 27:18.462
[yelps]

27:18.506 --> 27:20.116
[grunts]

27:20.160 --> 27:22.336
- With the recent death
of former football star

27:22.379 --> 27:24.860
Floyd Ferness,
San Bonifacio Police

27:24.904 --> 27:26.688
have officially closed
the investigation

27:26.732 --> 27:29.473
into the double car bombing
that left the city reeling.

27:29.517 --> 27:32.433
- However, Ferness is no
longer considered

27:32.476 --> 27:35.131
a prime suspect
in the recent zoo incident,

27:35.175 --> 27:37.481
as sources close
to the Ferness family have

27:37.525 --> 27:40.310
told us that Floyd could not
have perpetrated these crimes,

27:40.354 --> 27:43.270
as he has
a big game animal allergy.

27:43.313 --> 27:45.011
- Uh-huh.
Sí.

27:45.054 --> 27:47.709
- Animals included in this,
but not limited, are

27:47.753 --> 27:50.843
elephants,
marsupials, giraffes,...

27:50.886 --> 27:52.279
- [speaking Spanish]

27:52.322 --> 27:55.195
- Lizards,
including the gecko lizard,

27:55.238 --> 27:57.327
as well as the Cnemidophorus.

27:57.371 --> 28:01.636
Some fish, and insects
with eight or more legs.

28:02.376 --> 28:05.509
More on this later,
only on your number one

28:05.553 --> 28:08.295
news source, San Bonifacio,
Channel Eight.

28:08.338 --> 28:11.254
[tense music]

28:11.298 --> 28:13.996
♪

28:14.040 --> 28:15.302
- Ese,this isn't a charity.

28:15.345 --> 28:17.347
Okay?
I'm way out of pocket here.

28:17.391 --> 28:19.654
And I don't know how much
longer I can keep it up.

28:19.698 --> 28:26.748
♪

28:34.930 --> 28:37.890
[dreamy music]

28:37.933 --> 28:44.810
♪

28:45.941 --> 28:47.682
- [muffled scream]

28:47.726 --> 28:49.423
- [speaking Spanish]

29:00.042 --> 29:01.261
- [exhales]

29:04.003 --> 29:05.482
[knock on door]

29:07.571 --> 29:10.487
- Really making yourself
at home in here, huh, Gene?

29:10.531 --> 29:12.011
- Eh, something about
the Floyd Ferness story

29:12.054 --> 29:13.403
isn't sitting right.

29:13.447 --> 29:15.579
- Well, maybe you should have
thought about that

29:15.623 --> 29:17.668
before you shot him.

29:17.712 --> 29:20.149
- Chief, everyone shot him.

29:20.193 --> 29:22.717
- I know you lost a great deal.

29:22.761 --> 29:24.980
We all have.

29:25.024 --> 29:27.156
But here you are.

29:27.200 --> 29:28.897
Unscathed.

29:28.941 --> 29:31.421
With a great job,
beautiful wife,

29:31.465 --> 29:34.990
Who turned up and made a scene
at Felicity's funeral.

29:35.774 --> 29:38.298
- Are you saying
I can't control her?

29:38.341 --> 29:40.691
- Remind me why you transferred
here in the first place

29:40.735 --> 29:43.390
from back East?

29:43.433 --> 29:45.348
- I like it here, Chief.

29:45.392 --> 29:47.960
I've been able
to spread my wings.

29:52.355 --> 29:55.315
- Maybe it's time to fly
a little closer to the ground.

29:57.534 --> 29:58.797
- I don't know
what you're saying.

29:58.840 --> 30:00.755
- It's been a messy few weeks.

30:00.799 --> 30:03.584
Let's just try
and tidy things up, huh?

30:03.627 --> 30:05.760
Like, go have dinner
with your wife, Captain Colder.

30:05.804 --> 30:07.283
Buy her a steak.

30:07.327 --> 30:09.416
Woman like that could use
some red meat.

30:09.459 --> 30:10.939
[clicks tongue]

30:10.983 --> 30:12.941
And quit it
with the sugar water.

30:12.985 --> 30:14.769
Okay, you're gonna
give yourself diabetes.

30:14.813 --> 30:16.466
Lose a damn foot.

30:26.999 --> 30:29.915
[heavy rock music
on headphones]

30:29.958 --> 30:37.096
♪

30:42.928 --> 30:44.886
[knocking]

30:44.930 --> 30:46.496
- Hey.

30:46.540 --> 30:48.281
You're not supposed
to be back here.

30:48.324 --> 30:50.022
- Your boss said
you would talk to me.

30:50.065 --> 30:51.675
About Lalo Levantes.

30:51.719 --> 30:52.851
- [sighs]

30:52.894 --> 30:54.113
- You not a fan?

30:54.156 --> 30:55.505
- Nobody here is.

30:55.549 --> 30:57.899
Creep thinks he's
better than us.

30:57.943 --> 31:00.467
- No kidding.
Why is that?

31:00.510 --> 31:03.470
- Lalo worked a big bust with
Bonifacio P.D. a while back.

31:03.513 --> 31:05.864
And his head's been
swollen ever since.

31:05.907 --> 31:07.604
And guess who hung this up?

31:07.648 --> 31:10.129
He was pissed they cut him
out of the newspaper.

31:11.478 --> 31:14.437
[dramatic music]

31:14.481 --> 31:16.439
- He was there.

31:16.483 --> 31:17.571
- Looks like it.

31:19.703 --> 31:22.532
- Your boss said that
Lalo called in sick today.

31:22.576 --> 31:23.707
- [laughs]

31:23.751 --> 31:25.579
I saw him in the desert
this morning.

31:25.622 --> 31:27.668
Said he was camping.

31:27.711 --> 31:30.410
- Wait.
Where was this?

31:30.453 --> 31:32.891
When did you see him?

31:32.934 --> 31:34.414
Here's how I see it.

31:34.457 --> 31:36.285
Lalo helped bust
that drug outfit

31:36.329 --> 31:37.896
back at the
slaughterhouse.

31:37.939 --> 31:40.507
Then he filled
in the vacuum himself.

31:40.550 --> 31:43.205
He knows the border;
he knows the neighborhood.

31:43.249 --> 31:45.860
- And he paid for how many
high-powered drones?

31:45.904 --> 31:47.035
I don't know.

31:47.079 --> 31:49.951
- Felicity knew.

31:49.995 --> 31:52.432
She must have
confronted him about it.

31:52.475 --> 31:54.608
- Maybe we should bring
somebody else in on this.

31:54.651 --> 31:56.349
- No.

31:56.392 --> 31:58.220
Not yet.

32:00.092 --> 32:01.832
Drive to the press club.

32:01.876 --> 32:03.791
If Lalo was headed
into the desert this morning,

32:03.834 --> 32:05.314
then he's in the wind.

32:05.358 --> 32:07.577
Maybe his father can help us
figure out where he was going.

32:07.621 --> 32:10.929
- You can't prove Felicity
died because of this.

32:10.972 --> 32:13.583
You can't even prove
what this is.

32:13.627 --> 32:15.934
- I know what it is, okay?

32:15.977 --> 32:17.239
I've always known.

32:17.283 --> 32:19.938
Since I moved into this
hellhole, I've known.

32:21.548 --> 32:22.549
Don't be naive.

32:22.592 --> 32:25.726
- I am a black man
living in Texas.

32:25.769 --> 32:26.988
I know bad things happen.

32:27.032 --> 32:30.861
I'm just saying
we should slow down.

32:30.905 --> 32:33.081
Felicity, she was cautious.

32:33.125 --> 32:34.256
She was diligent.

32:34.300 --> 32:36.258
- Why did you come here?

32:36.302 --> 32:39.958
For the same reason
I came back, Singe.

32:41.655 --> 32:44.658
Death.

32:44.701 --> 32:46.703
This place is death.

32:48.227 --> 32:51.360
[dramatic music]

32:52.622 --> 32:55.495
[crickets chirping]

32:59.412 --> 33:00.979
- Wait a minute.
Wait, wait.

33:01.022 --> 33:03.111
Look, the afternoon edition.

33:09.726 --> 33:11.032
Laffter's saying Felicity
was bent.

33:11.076 --> 33:12.338
Strucker, too.

33:12.381 --> 33:14.166
Squeezing the Packingtown
criminals for a cut.

33:14.209 --> 33:16.211
Both in league with Floyd,
who blew them up

33:16.255 --> 33:17.299
when they iced him out.

33:17.343 --> 33:19.388
Why would Laffter write this?

33:21.347 --> 33:22.696
- Someone wanted it done.

33:28.049 --> 33:30.095
Nacho?

33:30.138 --> 33:31.574
You.
- Hey.

33:31.618 --> 33:33.054
Sorry, my dad had
an errand to run.

33:33.098 --> 33:34.403
I'll be out in a sec.

33:37.711 --> 33:38.755
What?

33:40.366 --> 33:43.151
- I know you're mixed up
in something.

33:43.195 --> 33:46.241
And I think that
Felicity figured it out.

33:49.375 --> 33:52.682
- [exhales]
- Freddie Laffter.

33:52.726 --> 33:54.728
- [scoffs]

33:54.771 --> 33:56.251
- Your story's a sham.

33:56.295 --> 33:58.949
- And what are you gonna
do about it, estate lawyer?

33:58.993 --> 34:00.168
You want me to bend over

34:00.212 --> 34:03.041
so you can manage my assets?

34:08.220 --> 34:11.179
- You will clear
Felicity Dill's name.

34:11.223 --> 34:12.789
Or you gonna wish that you had.

34:14.443 --> 34:16.706
- What do you think
you can do to me?

34:16.750 --> 34:19.057
I'm 73 years old.

34:21.407 --> 34:23.539
- How does a libel suit sound?

34:23.583 --> 34:26.194
Now, libel cases are
famously difficult to prove.

34:26.238 --> 34:29.415
But defending them takes money.

34:29.458 --> 34:32.200
Allegra Dill has recently come
into $1.7 million.

34:32.244 --> 34:34.376
Where does that leave you,
Mr. Laffter?

34:34.420 --> 34:36.117
Do you really think
the Staghornes

34:36.161 --> 34:37.771
are gonna waste a dime
of they fortune

34:37.814 --> 34:39.512
defending you?

34:39.555 --> 34:42.558
- You think I wanted
this piece of trash written?

34:43.777 --> 34:45.866
- Who did?

34:45.909 --> 34:48.564
- Felicity was my friend.
Why would I hurt her?

34:50.044 --> 34:52.655
- She knew what you were doing
at the slaughterhouse.

34:52.699 --> 34:55.397
Using drones to smuggle drugs.
- Drugs?

34:55.441 --> 34:58.139
- You're lying
to the border patrol, you're--

34:58.183 --> 35:00.576
- Hold up!
You went to my work?

35:00.620 --> 35:03.405
Who the hell
do you think you are?

35:03.449 --> 35:06.147
- You get nothing from me.
Nothing.

35:06.191 --> 35:08.410
- And that's what
you'll have, too.

35:08.454 --> 35:10.064
You'll be sucking down
creamed corn

35:10.108 --> 35:11.587
in the cheapest old-folks-home
in town,

35:11.631 --> 35:13.763
and they'll still be
wheeling your ass to court.

35:13.807 --> 35:16.505
You'll die bankrupt and alone
in a creaky twin bed,

35:16.549 --> 35:18.377
all because you
refused to retract

35:18.420 --> 35:21.641
this libelous, poorly written,
piece of shit article.

35:23.208 --> 35:24.731
- It was Raytek!

35:24.774 --> 35:26.863
It was the chief!

35:26.907 --> 35:28.865
She fed me the story.

35:28.909 --> 35:30.824
[coughing]

35:30.867 --> 35:32.260
You still wanna sue?

35:32.304 --> 35:35.133
You just go right ahead
and goddamn sue.

35:35.176 --> 35:36.743
[coughing]

35:36.786 --> 35:37.744
- You don't know me.

35:37.787 --> 35:38.875
You don't even
know your sister,

35:38.919 --> 35:40.921
and you think
I fucking killed her?

35:40.964 --> 35:42.401
The funeral is over.

35:42.444 --> 35:45.360
What are you still doing here?
Go home!

35:45.404 --> 35:47.145
[distant crash]

35:47.188 --> 35:49.886
[dramatic music]

35:49.930 --> 35:51.975
- Oh, my God.

35:52.019 --> 35:53.890
- Call an ambulance!

35:53.934 --> 35:56.632
- [groaning]

36:09.732 --> 36:11.908
- [sighs]
Give me that.

36:14.302 --> 36:15.956
[exhales]

36:18.393 --> 36:20.656
- You dragged me around
the underbelly of this city.

36:20.700 --> 36:22.049
And for what?

36:22.092 --> 36:24.747
We helped Clyde Brattle
succeed in messing with you.

36:24.791 --> 36:26.488
And I let you pull me
into your crazy.

36:26.532 --> 36:28.838
- The clues just didn't lead
where I expected.

36:30.362 --> 36:33.016
I don't know why.
- I know why.

36:33.060 --> 36:34.366
You're spinning.

36:35.802 --> 36:37.064
- What?

36:37.107 --> 36:38.500
- You're shaking
down teenagers.

36:38.544 --> 36:39.936
And you threatened
an old German man

36:39.980 --> 36:42.374
'cause you so desperate
to find something, anything,

36:42.417 --> 36:44.158
that'll keep you from
dealing with the truth.

36:44.202 --> 36:45.507
- What truth?

36:45.551 --> 36:47.770
- An awful thing happened.

36:49.119 --> 36:51.383
And you can't fix it.
- I can--

36:51.426 --> 36:54.168
- You've got to sit
with the grief, Allegra.

36:54.212 --> 36:55.430
You've got to sit with it.

36:55.474 --> 36:57.519
It's ugly.
It's painful.

36:57.563 --> 36:59.260
But that is the only way

36:59.304 --> 37:01.697
that you're gonna deal
with your shit!

37:04.874 --> 37:06.136
- [scoffs]

37:06.180 --> 37:07.964
What about your shit?

37:09.401 --> 37:12.447
You live in a dollhouse!

37:12.491 --> 37:15.581
I may not be sitting around
drowning in my loss,

37:15.624 --> 37:17.713
but at least I'm not stuck.

37:17.757 --> 37:19.367
- I ain't stuck.

37:19.411 --> 37:20.890
Hey, don't touch that.

37:20.934 --> 37:23.241
Allegra, put that back.

37:23.284 --> 37:25.025
[funky music]

37:25.068 --> 37:26.505
Put that down.

37:29.943 --> 37:31.379
Allegra!

37:33.120 --> 37:35.905
Don't touch it.

37:35.949 --> 37:37.167
Stop!

37:37.211 --> 37:39.082
I said--I said--

37:39.126 --> 37:41.781
I said, "Stop."

37:43.173 --> 37:45.088
Stop!
- No!

37:45.132 --> 37:46.264
- I told--

37:46.307 --> 37:48.483
[toys clattering]

37:48.527 --> 37:51.312
I told you to stop.

37:51.356 --> 37:52.792
- No.

37:52.835 --> 37:59.799
♪

38:40.187 --> 38:41.623
- You know you'll be on the--

38:41.667 --> 38:42.972
Anyway, I don't need
to describe it.

38:43.016 --> 38:44.278
But, you know what--
[laughs]

38:44.322 --> 38:49.022
Just see what a little--
[laughs]

38:49.065 --> 38:50.328
Oh, okay, cool.

38:54.593 --> 38:56.986
[fast-forwarding audio]

38:57.030 --> 38:59.032
We have to talk.

38:59.075 --> 39:01.469
I need help.

39:01.513 --> 39:03.471
No, not there.
It's not safe.

39:03.515 --> 39:05.386
Meet me in Packingtown.

39:06.866 --> 39:09.216
No, not there.
It's not safe.

39:09.259 --> 39:11.174
Meet me in Packingtown.

39:11.218 --> 39:13.089
Meet me in Packingtown.

39:16.266 --> 39:19.182
[soft dramatic music]

39:19.226 --> 39:23.796
♪

39:23.839 --> 39:26.364
- You looking
for something, ma'am?

39:26.407 --> 39:28.017
- Whatever it is that I missed.

39:28.061 --> 39:30.672
- Don't make me tell you again!
Get off the table!

39:33.458 --> 39:36.548
[indistinct chatter]

39:49.169 --> 39:56.089
♪

40:00.702 --> 40:02.791
[crickets chirping]

41:16.256 --> 41:19.215
[tense music]

41:19.259 --> 41:26.179
♪

41:33.229 --> 41:36.406
[distant metal clattering]

41:36.450 --> 41:39.497
[children laughing]

41:41.542 --> 41:44.545
[children speaking Spanish]

41:52.597 --> 41:59.691
♪

42:05.392 --> 42:08.787
[indistinct whispering]

42:24.237 --> 42:31.157
♪

42:34.552 --> 42:36.075
- You shouldn't
have come here.

42:39.382 --> 42:41.820
[electricity crackling]
